# Work_Sample_Simulation

It is a simple bash script to look for an specific IP address on sshd log.


#############################################################################

The script should will  display a count of login attempts from an IP address, where the <ip-address>
is the input variable that can be passed in to search through a ssh log file.

###############################################################################


The script will follow these steps:

1) Define the log file to use 
2) Get the ip address from user input 
3) Count the number of login attemtps for the specific IP address 
4) Display the result to user output


For any issues, contact helloit@helloyou.com



